    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1877-11-16T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1877-11-16T00:00:00-05:00" n="110" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d110">
                <head>No. 105.<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Noyes</persName>
                            to Mr. <persName type="to">Evarts</persName>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of
                                    the United States</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Paris</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1877-11-16">
                            <hi rend="italic">November</hi> 16, 1877</date>.
                            (Received November 28.)</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 29.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>Sir: Since writing the dispatch No. 28, of this date, information reaches me
                        that the entire ministry have again tendered their resignations, and that
                        the same have been or will be accepted by the President. As the <pb facs="0226" n="164" xml:id="pg_164"/> mail closes in a few minutes, I
                        have no time to obtain further particulars or information, but will do so at
                        the earliest practicable moment.</p>
                <p>I have, &amp;c.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>EDWARD F. NOYES.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
